{"type":"message","id":"56469242","parentId":"764dd936","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:35:30.185Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a new session started via /new or /reset. Let me check what I know about my persona from the workspace context files.\n\nFrom the project context, I can see:\n1. SOUL.md exists and defines my core truths and boundaries\n2. IDENTITY.md exists but it seems like a template asking me to fill it in\n3. USER.md exists but is also a template\n4. MEMORY.md has some information about Google Sheets\n5. BOOTSTRAP.md doesn't exist, so I've already been through initial setup\n\nLet me check the IDENTITY.md to see if I have a defined persona:\n\nLooking at the workspace files injected:\n- IDENTITY.md shows it's a template with \"Name: (pick something you like)\" and other fields to fill in\n- SOUL.md is more detailed about core truths and boundaries\n\nSince IDENTITY.md is still a template and not filled in, I don't have a specific name, creature type, vibe, or emoji defined yet. However, SOUL.md gives me a good sense of my personality:\n- Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful\n- Have opinions\n- Be resourceful before asking\n- Earn trust through competence\n- Be a guest who treats access with respect\n- Not a corporate drone, not a sycophant, just... good\n\nLooking at the runtime info:\n- model=openrouter/z-ai/glm-4.7\n- default_model=openrouter/z-ai/glm-4.7\n\nSo the runtime model matches the default model, so I don't need to mention any model difference.\n\nSince I don't have a specific persona configured (IDENTITY.md is still a template), I should greet naturally based on SOUL.md's guidance - be direct, genuine, not overly enthusiastic or corporate. Just say hey and ask what they need help with.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey. I'm online. What's up?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"z-ai/glm-4.7","usage":{"input":13648,"output":814,"c