{"type":"message","id":"02a8164a","parentId":"7db7f143","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:36:49.501Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The lease.js script is heavily commented out. It seems like most of the actual updating of sheets is commented out, and only the PDF generation and email sending are active. Let me check what format is expected by looking at the regex patterns in the script.\n\nBased on the script, the expected format seems to be:\n- Format 1: \"TenantName has leased apartment [address] Room [number] from [date] to [date] for [amount] number [contact] email [email]\"\n- Format 2: \"Apartment [address] to TenantName from [date] to [date] for [amount] number [contact] email [email]\"\n\nThe user's input is: \"Apartment 90 Washington room 1 to Usman from 11/11/2026 to 12/12/2026 for 1200$. Zayan contact is 3271630656 and emails is zayanyaseen99@gmail.com.\"\n\nLet me format this properly for the lease command. Looking at the regex:\n- apartment: matches \"apartment (.*?) Room\" or \"apartment (.*?) to\" or \"apartment (.*?) from\"\n- tenantName: matches \"(.*?) has leased\" or \" to ([a-z .'-]+?) from\"\n- room: matches \"Room (\\d+)\"\n- startDate: matches \"from (.*?) to\"\n- endDate: matches \"from\\s+\\d{1,2}\\/\\d{1,2}\\/\\d{4}\\s+to\\s+(\\d{1,2}\\/\\d{1,2}\\/\\d{4})\"\n- amount: matches \"(?:amount|for)\\s*\\$?(\\d+)\"\n- contact: matches \"(?:number|contact)\\s*(?:is)?\\s*(\\d+)\"\n- email: matches \"(?:email|emails)\\s*(?:is)?\\s*([^\\s$.]+@[^\\s$.]+\\.[^\\s$.]+)\"\n \nI'll construct the command precisely matching the script's expected pattern, ensuring all key details are captured in the correct format.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll add this lease to the system. Let me format the command properly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6a58c38b0985439eaa547621","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\MudasserRasool\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\google-sheets-api\"; n